http://nativeclient.googlecode.com/files/nacl_linux_0.1_9308700.tgz

&lt;b&gt;On what operating system?&lt;/b&gt;
Fedora 8

&lt;b&gt;What browser are you using?&lt;/b&gt;
Opera 10.00, Firefox 2.0.0.18

&lt;b&gt;What steps will reproduce the problem?&lt;/b&gt;
1. Uncompress the package
2. cd nacl/googleclient/native_client/tests/earth
3. Run 'python run.py'


&lt;b&gt;What is the expected output? What do you see instead?&lt;/b&gt;
Expected output is that the application runs. Instead I get the following 
error: /opt/nacl/googleclient/native_client/scons-out/dbg-linux/staging/
sel_ldr: error while loading shared libraries: libssl.so.0.9.8: cannot 
open shared object file: No such file or directory

If I create the necessary symlinks libssl.so.0.9.8 -&amp;gt; libssl.so and 
libcrypto.so.0.9.8 -&amp;gt; libcrypto.so it runs correctly.

But then, after installing the native client plugin, I get this error: 
/root/.mozilla/plugins/sel_ldr_bin: /usr/lib/libcrypto.so.0.9.8: no 
version information available (required by /root/.mozilla/plugins/
sel_ldr_bin)
No nacl file specified


And if I try to load the plugin in Opera, it just crashes. In firefox I 
get a grey box where the embeded application should be.

